-- CTC Media’s Russia TV Audience Shares Steady, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 2012-07-19T22:24:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-19/ctc-media-s-russia-tv-audience-shares-steady-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel remained the sixth most-watched among Russian viewers 18
years and older in the week to July 15, according to TNS-Global.  Viewer share for CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, slipped to 5.4 percent in
the week to July 15, from 5.5 percent in the previous week, data
researcher TNS-Global said by e-mail today.  CTC’s average daily audience among viewers 4 years old and
over was unchanged at 5.9 percent in the week, the data show.
CTC remained in fifth place among viewers 4 years old and over,
TNS-Global said.  Russia’s NTV Television was the most watched among both
audience categories while government-controlled Pervyi Kanal was
the second in each group. Rossiya-1, also government-controlled,
was the third-most watched in both segments and TNT TV was
fourth, the data show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
